is the existence of a critical $\\alpha$ (which we denote by $\\alpha\n_c=-0.3182$) such that the distribution exhibits a local maximum at $t_r = t/2$\nfor $\\alpha < \\alpha _c$\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Nov 2021 20:42:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 6 Feb 2022 06:57:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-14"}
