{"id":"2112.01323","submitter":"Hong-Wei Zhang","authors":"Jean-Philippe Anker, Effie Papageorgiou, Hong-Wei Zhang","title":"Asymptotic behavior of solutions to the heat equation on noncompact\n  symmetric spaces","comments":"To appear in J. Funct. Anal","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.jfa.2022.109828","report-no":null,"categories":"math.AP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/","abstract":"  This paper is twofold. The first part aims to study the long-time asymptotic\nbehavior of solutions to the heat equation on Riemannian symmetric spaces $G/K$\nof noncompact type and of general rank. We show that any solution to the heat\nequation with bi-$K$-invariant $L^{1}$ initial data behaves asymptotically as\nthe mass times the fundamental solution, and provide a counterexample in the\nnon bi-$K$-invariant case. These answer problems recently raised by J.L.\nV\\'azquez. In the second part, we investigate the long-time asymptotic behavior\nof solutions to the heat equation associated with the so-called distinguished\nLaplacian on $G/K$. Interestingly, we observe in this case phenomena which are\nsimilar to the Euclidean setting, namely $L^1$ asymptotic convergence with no\nbi-$K$-invariance condition and strong $L^{\\infty}$ convergence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 01:09:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Dec 2022 16:12:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
